critical_positive: Nicholas was an interesting person, who I genuinely wanted to know more about. He was very friendly and open to talk about whatever came up. Nothing felt forced, we just dove right into conversation like we knew each other very well. It was laidback and free flowing. No one really dominated the conversation and it was a good back and forth.
critical_negative: Honestly nothing bad to say other than the initial hiccup with the video and audio not connecting. The only issues were in my head worrying if I was saying anything dumb. It was a long day for me so, I had to take some pauses to think about my words and thoughts.

rest_of_day_open: It will be stressful at first and then decline into a nice calm towards the end. critical_positive: We really clicked right off the bat.  We didn't even introduce ourselves until the very end of the conversation, and that was just when we had realized we had been talking for over half an hour without knowing the other person's name.  We also had shared interests that helped support the rest of the conversation from then on.
critical_negative: There were a few moments where the conversation dipped as we exhausted the current topic.  Also, I feel like I was saying a lot about myself and took up too much time, not giving my partner a chance to similarly respond.  I tried asking him questions about his life, but it seemed like most of what he was interested in was discussing my answers further.
